cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.RO

The paper presents a novel approach for imposing physically motivated inductive biases on graph networks to learn interpretable representations and improved zero-shot generalization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with symbolic regression and inferring explicit causal theories, which suggests that it may also belong to the systems and control (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses deep learning techniques to learn unknown interaction laws, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
